title: Arbitrary "Lines" in Ecology, Ethics, and Animal Rights. (Vegan)
description: To say something is arbitrary doesn't mean that it's evil, nor that it's even wrong.  Especially in the habitat-conservation approach to animal rights, we often deal with distinctions that are entirely arbitrary, and entirely man-made.
